# =============================================================================
# Chrono Lexicanum — .gitignore
# Rule of thumb: ANYTHING that is local-only, regenerable, secret, or scratch.
# Nothing in /sessions/ — those are the project's history and SHOULD be in git.
# =============================================================================

# --- dependencies ------------------------------------------------------------
/node_modules
/.pnp
.pnp.*
.yarn/*
!.yarn/patches
!.yarn/plugins
!.yarn/releases
!.yarn/versions

# --- next.js / build artefacts ----------------------------------------------
/.next/
/out/
/build
/coverage
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# --- secrets -----------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env*.local

# --- vercel ------------------------------------------------------------------
.vercel

# --- editor / OS -------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.pem

# --- Obsidian (per-user vault config; brain/ may be opened as a vault) ------
.obsidian/

# --- Claude Code (per-user state; shared settings.json / hooks / agents -----
# can be committed deliberately by removing the line below if/when they exist) -
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/*.lock

# --- scratch logs (dev-server probes etc.) ----------------------------------
*.log

# --- npm / debug logs --------------------------------------------------------
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# --- prototype archive (kept locally as reference, NOT in repo) -------------
# The original HTML/JSX prototype lives under /archive/. The data has already
# been extracted to /scripts/seed-data/*.json which IS committed. Keep the
# prototype on your disk for reference, but never push it.
/archive/

# --- design exports (local reference material, never committed) -------------
# Cowork design-direction exports (HTML/CSS/JSX + assets) land here for the
# port sessions. Reference-only, like /archive/ — keep local, never push.
# Gitignoring also keeps Tailwind v4 source-detection from scanning them.
/design-export/

# --- presentations / standalone explainers (local-only, never committed) ----
# Self-contained HTML decks Cowork builds for Philipp (e.g. the data-provenance
# explainer). Offline reference material like /design-export/ — keep local,
# never push. Gitignoring also keeps Tailwind v4 source-detection from scanning.
/presentation/

# --- scratch / drafts (anything you want to try without committing) --------
.scratch/
*.scratch.*
/screenshots-local/
/sessions/_drafts/
/reviews/

# --- timeline-workshop (Cowork+Philipp manual Chronicle dating) -------------
# Cowork and Philipp curate the in-universe events spine + per-book setting
# dates here BY HAND, across sessions, OUTSIDE git — so CC can keep working the
# 121/122 boards in parallel without collisions. This is exploratory curation,
# not a committed dataset; when a clean events set + a proven per-book dating
# procedure emerge, they graduate into a proper Batches brief (events table +
# apply path). The work-in-progress is intentionally never committed.
/timeline-workshop/

# --- sitewide MediaPlayer audio (large binaries, repo is public) -----------
# MP3/WAV/OGG tracks under public/audio/ are NOT committed: ~25 MB of binaries
# in a public repo's permanent history + unclear rights. The README.md (how to
# add tracks) IS kept. Host the tracks externally or add them at deploy time.
/public/audio/*.mp3
/public/audio/*.wav
/public/audio/*.ogg
/public/audio/*.m4a

# --- ingestion pipeline cache (regenerable, can be huge) -------------------
/scripts/.cache/
/ingest/.cache/

# --- LLM-Anreicherungs-Cache (Phase 3c) ------------------------------------
# Cached Tool-Use-Antworten der Anthropic-API pro Buch, regenerierbar (jede
# Prompt-Änderung invalidiert den Cache via Hash). Kann gross werden bei
# 800-Buch-Voll-Lauf, deshalb wie /ingest/.cache/ gitignored.
/ingest/.llm-cache/

# --- cc-direct podcast tagging working files (Brief 131) --------------------
# run-podcast-tag-loop.sh + podcast-cc-tag.ts stage per-run working files here
# (the acquire manifest + per-batch input/output). Regenerated each run; the
# committed contract is ingest/podcasts/<slug>.extractions.json, not these.
/ingest/podcasts/.cc-tag/

# --- cc-direct book-reviewer working files (Brief 154) ----------------------
# run-book-review-loop.sh + book-review.ts stage per-run working files here
# (projected chunk inputs + per-chunk finder/findings/verifier). Regenerated
# each run; the committed outputs are scripts/seed-data/book-review-queue.json
# + facet-review-queue.json + scripts/logs/book-review-log.md, not these.
/ingest/book-review/.work/

# --- cc-direct book-reviewer HUMAN-REVIEW slices (regenerable, deletable) ----
# review-digest .md files Philipp eyeballs then deletes; never committed.
/ingest/book-review/review/

# --- ingestion pipeline state (resumable run state, NOT diffs) -------------
# /ingest/.state/ holds the in-progress run snapshot — regenerated each run,
# wiped on success, irrelevant to other developers. Diffs in /ingest/.last-run/
# ARE committed (proof-of-run + audit trail).
/ingest/.state/

# --- per-book SSOT equivalence proof artifacts (Brief 171) ------------------
# scripts/equivalence-diff.ts writes its projection-diff report + DB snapshots
# here. Regenerated on every run, never a corpus source — kept out of git so it
# never gets mistaken for the committed ingest/.last-run/ digests. The report
# content is reproduced in the impl report as the named proof artifact.
/ingest/.equivalence/

# --- per-book read-only Excel export (Brief 171) ----------------------------
# scripts/books-excel.ts renders books/*.json into a reference .xlsx here. ONE-WAY
# export (Excel is no longer the SSOT), regenerated on demand — never committed.
/ingest/.exports/

# --- loop-driver step log (Brief 071) --------------------------------------
# scripts/run-ssot-loop.sh tees its stdout into this file for post-mortem
# inspection. Per-run, regenerated on every invocation, irrelevant in git.
/scripts/.last-loop-run.log
/scripts/.last-resolver-pass.log
/scripts/.last-resolver-loop.log

# --- resolver-pass state file (Brief 094) ----------------------------------
# scripts/run-resolver-pass.sh writes per-phase progress here so the
# resolver-loop wrapper can record outcomes in sessions/resolver-loop-log.md.
# Regenerated on every invocation; irrelevant in git.
/scripts/.last-resolver-pass-state.json

# --- preview-invite console output (Brief 163) ------------------------------
# scripts/preview-console/build.mjs generates console.html from the committed,
# secret-free template.html. The generated file is what Philipp opens locally
# (`npm run preview:console`); it is never deployed and never committed. The
# committed source of truth is template.html + build.mjs + serve.mjs.
/scripts/preview-console/console.html

# Playwright (S8 mini smoke set)
/test-results/
/playwright-report/
